headline.main: 7 Vessels Sunk, 5 Damaged In New Attacks Off Italy; British Submarines Get Another Destroyer and Four Troop or Supply Craft -- Week's Naval Toll Rises to 19

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 11 -- Four troop or supply ships, plus two sailing vessels and an Italian destroyer, have been sunk in the Mediterranean since the brilliant convoy action of last Sunday, the Admiralty announced today. This time it was British submarines that attacked.
abstract: Brit submarines sink 6 Axis ships, 1 Ital destroyer, damage 5, Mediterranean; RAF bombs Sicily and southern Italy targets; Rome confirms raids
